  centered in the adaptive-icon safe zone. Same glyph as the QS tile
  (ic_tile_cliptic.xml), scaled from its 24x24 box into the 108 viewport
  (scale 1.6667, translate 34 → a 40dp mark centered on 54,54).

  The fill uses the Android 12+ Material You system palette
  (@android:color/system_accent1_600 ≈ the wallpaper's "primary" tone) so the
  mark is tinted to the device's dynamic colors out of the box — not only when
  the launcher's "Themed icons" toggle is on (that path is the monochrome layer).
-->
